1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,433
<i>- Lieutenant Conde!
- What is it, Enriquez?</i>

2
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:16,467
<i> Where is Faye?</i>

3
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:18,467
<i> We've been outsmarted.</i>

4
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:20,833
<i> It's Faye.</i>

5
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,100
<i>Let's find a way
through the back!</i>

6
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,300
<i> Enriquez, come on!</i>

7
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> I'll help Lieutenant Conde!</i>

8
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:39,600
<i>You two, you're really stubborn.</i>

9
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,633
<i> Major, assign Conde</i>

10
00:00:41,767 --> 00:00:44,333
<i>to the investigation team for
the San Isidro bank robbery.</i>

11
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:46,067
<i> I need a top cop on this.</i>

12
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,567
<i>- Thank you, Mayor.
- It's no use, Joaquin.</i>

13
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:50,867
<i> The damage has been done.</i>

14
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,900
<i> Can I call you sister?</i>

15
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:54,033
<i> Of course.</i>

16
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:55,967
<i>And I haven't even
thanked you yet.</i>

17
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,467
<i>Don't mention it, Lieutenant
Conde.</i>

18
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,800
<i> Just call me Tonyo.</i>

19
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,567
<i>Doesn't Sergeant Bobby Enriquez
look like someone?</i>

20
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:03,867
<i>- Who?
- Your mistress, Amanda.</i>

21
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,300
<i> Forensics sent a message.</i>

22
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:06,833
<i>They say the ballistics
results are in.</i>

23
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
<i> What did they say?</i>

24
00:01:08,133 --> 00:01:10,400
<i>It links him to the San Isidro
bank robbery.</i>

25
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:38,467
Mayor...

26
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:41,933
Would it be okay
if we take a selfie?

27
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:44,367
- Go ahead.
- Really?

28
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,533
Okay, let's do it here.

29
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:50,200
I'm nervous, Mayor, but okay!

30
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:53,833
- There!
- Can we do it like this?

31
00:01:53,967 --> 00:01:56,300
Sure.

32
00:01:56,433 --> 00:01:57,433
Oh my gosh.

33
00:01:57,567 --> 00:01:59,733
Oh, Mayor...

34
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:02,767
I just want you to know...

35
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:05,467
you still have my vote.

36
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:08,100
Thank you so much, Nurse.

37
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:10,800
It's a great honor for me.

38
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,067
Thank you so much.

39
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,567
Okay, I'll get going now.

40
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:23,100
Major, is it true...

41
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,767
that this is...

42
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:30,667
one of the member of the group
who robbed the San Isidro bank?

43
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,233
Yes, Mayor.

44
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:38,333
Therefore, this counts
as hard evidence, correct?

45
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,567
Yes, Mayor.

46
00:02:44,767 --> 00:02:48,300
I think this is the justice
we've been waiting for...

47
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:52,567
for the victims of
the San Isidro robbery.

48
00:02:53,233 --> 00:02:57,967
And Major, I want you to know
that you need...

49
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:02,367
to get every piece of
information

50
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:05,500
from this person.

51
00:03:05,633 --> 00:03:08,767
I want this to be solved...

52
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,000
before the election begins.

53
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:12,667
Do you understand?

54
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,867
And one more thing,

55
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,800
The people of the City of
Calabari must know...

56
00:03:18,933 --> 00:03:21,033
that justice will prevail.

57
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,233
You can count on us, Mayor.

58
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:26,333
Our team won't let you down.

59
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,167
- Call the nurse!
- Nurse! Nurse!

60
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:30,200
<i> Doc Ralph, please proceed</i>

61
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,333
<i> to the emergency room.</i>

62
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,867
<i> Hey, did you know?</i>

63
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,300
<i>I hope that I get to administer
the medication</i>

64
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:53,700
<i>to the kidnapper later
when the Mayor's around.</i>

65
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,467
<i> He's really my idol.</i>

66
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,533
<i>Just go there,
I heard that he's on his way.</i>

67
00:04:57,667 --> 00:04:58,600
<i> Stay there...</i>

68
00:04:58,733 --> 00:04:59,967
<i>I'll grab the medication
for the patient.</i>

69
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,933
<i>- Let's go.
- Let's go.</i>

70
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,533
- Faye!
- Let me go...

71
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,200
- Faye, Faye!
- Oh! Let me go!

72
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,133
- I don't want to!
- Faye!

73
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:21,933
I'm here, I'm here, I'm here.

74
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:23,833
You're safe, you're safe.

75
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:26,500
You're safe, you're safe,
you're safe, you're safe.

76
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:28,567
I'm here. I'm here.

77
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,733
You're safe, you're safe.

78
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:33,767
Breathe, breathe,
breathe, breathe, breathe.

79
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:37,233
You're okay.

80
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:42,167
You're okay.

81
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:44,967
You're okay.

82
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:48,900
Faye...

83
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:55,133
I can't imagine
what you've gone through.

84
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:59,467
But I know that you need
justice...

85
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,600
for you to have your closure.

86
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,367
So if there's...

87
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:08,333
anything you remember,

88
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:11,100
aside from the kidnappers
we've caught...

89
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:14,033
Tell me, okay?

90
00:06:14,467 --> 00:06:15,733
Tell me.

91
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:19,567
You understand?

92
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:36,500
Time of death, 10:17 a.m.

93
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:38,900
He's supposed to be
on his way to recovery.

94
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,767
Are you sure you gave
the right medication?

95
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:45,167
Yes, Doc.
I couldn't have made a mistake.

96
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,100
Come with me.

97
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:48,500
Explain it to Dr. Chelsea.

98
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:50,233
Excuse me, Mayor.

99
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:02,367
Before he was brought to the
hospital...

100
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,800
it's like he wanted
to say something...

101
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:09,367
Something about a powerful
person behind all this.

102
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:12,233
Then, suddenly,
he stopped breathing.

103
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,200
It's strange.

104
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:20,233
Unless someone
didn't want him to speak.

105
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:24,867
Major, order
a hospital lockdown.

106
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,933
Lockdown, Sir?

107
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:28,467
Yes.

108
00:07:29,367 --> 00:07:31,900
No one goes in,
no one goes out

109
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:35,533
until whoever did
this is caught.

110
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:51,533
Apologies, Mayor...

111
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:54,400
But we can't lock down
the hospital.

112
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,533
Okay.

113
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:57,800
Just make sure

114
00:07:57,933 --> 00:08:00,300
that before the day ends,

115
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:05,133
I would know who did this.

116
00:08:07,267 --> 00:08:08,833
Yes, Mayor.

117
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,433
Lieutenant Conde,

118
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:13,600
Sergeant Enriquez,

119
00:08:13,733 --> 00:08:15,833
we're all victims here.

120
00:08:16,267 --> 00:08:18,400
Don't fail me.

121
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:20,900
- Yes, Sir.
- Yes, Sir.

122
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:24,367
I'll just be in the
director's office, okay?

123
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:26,333
Yes, Sir.

124
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,900
Listen up!

125
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,867
Dizon, Noble,
cover the main entrance.

126
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,933
Get the names of everyone

127
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:38,833
who went in and out
of the hospital

128
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:41,133
in the last 24 hours.

129
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:45,167
Robles, I want to know
everything about this kidnapper.

130
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,267
Start with their name.

131
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:51,100
Garcia, check
all the CCTV footage

132
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:52,767
for the last 24 hours.

133
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,967
24 hours, Sir?

134
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:58,933
Okay, even if it's long,
I can handle it.

135
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,433
Conde, Enriquez,

136
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,867
interview all hospital staff.

137
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,600
I want to know
who had access to our kidnapper.

138
00:09:08,733 --> 00:09:10,433
- Yes, Sir.
- Go! Move!

139
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:24,767
Doctor...

140
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:27,133
we need your help here.

141
00:09:31,433 --> 00:09:33,867
Well, that's all I can say,
Detectives.

142
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,233
If you have more questions,

143
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:38,167
I'll be in my clinic
until 10 p.m.

144
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,133
Just come find me.

145
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:41,767
- All right.
- Thank you, Doc.

146
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,300
Thank you.

147
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:54,367
Nice, you're taking notes.

148
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:57,900
Can you not judge me, Sir?

149
00:09:58,033 --> 00:09:59,933
My mentor taught me this.

150
00:10:00,067 --> 00:10:02,533
Note everything
you can note down...

151
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,200
it helps keep
thoughts organized.

152
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,533
Okay!

153
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:11,033
Sir...

154
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:14,133
She trained me
as an investigator.

155
00:10:14,567 --> 00:10:15,700
If she were here now,

156
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:18,367
she'd definitely be proud of me.

157
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,800
It's just ironic that her case

158
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,967
is the first I have to solve.

159
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,300
It's just a shame, Sir.

160
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:26,733
I thought we were finally going
to get

161
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:28,433
the name of the kidnapper.

162
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:29,867
But he died.

163
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,900
Even from the dead,

164
00:10:32,033 --> 00:10:34,633
you can still
squeeze out information...

165
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,633
if you know where to look.

166
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,833
Who's next for the interview?

167
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:46,333
Sir, the nurse is here.

168
00:10:51,667 --> 00:10:53,133
Garcia.

169
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:56,967
I'll go with you.

170
00:10:57,533 --> 00:10:59,900
You and your moves.

171
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:00,933
You just idolize me.

172
00:11:01,067 --> 00:11:03,767
You want to see the moves.

173
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:07,500
All right, I'll show you.
Come on.

174
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:13,233
Let me show you
how a real detective does it.

175
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,300
Hey, Sir.

176
00:11:17,433 --> 00:11:18,633
Bosses, we're sorry...

177
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:22,267
but we need to check your CCTV.

178
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,233
Sure, Sir.

179
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:25,000
Please wait outside for a bit.

180
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:40,267
Ma'am, Sir, I swear

181
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,867
I have no idea about that.

182
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:43,900
It's impossible...

183
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:46,533
that I gave the patient
the wrong medication.

184
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:47,867
I've been a nurse
for a long time,

185
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,900
I know what I'm doing.

186
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:51,933
It's really impossible
for me to make that mistake.

187
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:54,100
Please believe me.

188
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:56,367
Where were the medication
taken from, exactly?

189
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:02,000
Nurse Pam, right?

190
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:04,133
According to my notes...

191
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:05,433
your friends said,

192
00:12:05,567 --> 00:12:07,833
all the medication were taken
from the hospital pharmacy?

193
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:09,133
Yes, Ma'am.
That's correct.

194
00:12:09,267 --> 00:12:11,500
All of it came
from the pharmacy.

195
00:12:18,033 --> 00:12:20,000
Here's what we can do,
Nurse Pam.

196
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:25,000
Let's say someone wanted to swap
out the medication

197
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:26,900
meant for the patient.

198
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:30,667
Where and when would be
the safest time to do it?

199
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,567
Sometimes,

200
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:35,233
we leave medicine at the nurse's
station

201
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:37,233
while waiting for the right time

202
00:12:37,367 --> 00:12:39,000
to administer
them to the patient.

203
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,767
It's possible someone got access

204
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,167
when no nurse was watching.

205
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:47,933
Sir, we should check the CCTV
at the nurse's station.

206
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,667
I've already sent out all
the kidnapper's photos.

207
00:12:53,367 --> 00:12:55,333
Match them against all records,

208
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:58,133
and also cross-check with known

209
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:04,467
associates of
Sebastian “Batsi” Placido, okay?

210
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,300
Thank you.

211
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:14,700
Hey, it's Nurse Cutie.

212
00:13:22,467 --> 00:13:23,733
Idol!

213
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:27,333
Want me to take over for a bit?

214
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,867
Told you you're my idol.

215
00:13:31,533 --> 00:13:34,700
This is kind of making me
sleepy, anyway.

216
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:36,667
Yes, you've been here a while.

217
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:37,567
Take a break if you want.

218
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,233
Grab some coffee.

219
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:40,467
- Here.
- Oh, your treat?

220
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,533
My treat.

221
00:13:41,667 --> 00:13:44,467
Wow! Oh my,
this is enough for two coffees.

222
00:13:45,167 --> 00:13:46,433
All right, I'll go grab some.

223
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,833
Keep me posted, okay?

224
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:59,000
Sir, here's the visitor's
logbook from yesterday.

225
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,467
Thank you.

226
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,533
Miss, miss, media isn't allowed.

227
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:06,833
Seriously?

228
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:08,700
The people deserve
to know the truth!

229
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,333
Can you please just step aside?

230
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:12,833
I'm telling you,
it's not allowed.

231
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:17,533
<i> Paging Doctor Gutierrez...</i>

232
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:18,500
All right, Ma'am.

233
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:20,600
I'll just stay here.
I won't leave.

234
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:22,933
It's up to you...

235
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:30,733
Mayor, do you want anything
for lunch?

236
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:32,700
We can request it from
the canteen.

237
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:33,700
Thanks, Doc.

238
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:35,533
I think I'll just eat outside.

239
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:36,833
- Okay, I'll leave you then.
- Okay.

240
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:38,367
Okay.

241
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:42,233
So rude.

242
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,433
- Good afternoon, Doc.
- Good afternoon.

243
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:02,133
Good afternoon.

244
00:16:18,733 --> 00:16:20,167
Enriquez!

245
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:22,000
Enriquez!

246
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:25,867
Looks like you really missed me.

247
00:16:26,267 --> 00:16:28,133
Oh, I just went out
to get coffee.

248
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:29,333
No, I'm good, Sir.

249
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:30,500
Thank you.

250
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:31,933
Oh, this isn't for you...

251
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,500
it's for me and Robles.

252
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:36,033
The CCTV footage is
making me sleepy.

253
00:16:36,867 --> 00:16:38,533
So, what are you guys
doing here?

254
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:41,433
We need to check
the nurse's station CCTV.

255
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,133
Come on, Bok.

256
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,100
All right.

257
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,733
Robles!

258
00:16:50,867 --> 00:16:52,967
We've got guests here.

259
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:57,633
No change left.

260
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:59,333
They said it was exact.

261
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:02,400
Mind if we check the CCTV?

262
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:03,767
Hold on, Bok.

263
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:05,033
What's going on?

264
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:07,533
I feel like I've been noticing
you guys a lot today.

265
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:10,367
Bok, just to be clear...

266
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:13,100
if you guys find a lead
in there...

267
00:17:13,233 --> 00:17:16,233
- me...
- All the credit goes to you.

268
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,667
There, now we're clear.

269
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,133
You can really count on
these guys, Bok.

270
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:22,367
All right then!

271
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,867
Have a seat.

272
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:43,100
There! There!

273
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:45,733
There, that's the
nurse's station.

274
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,433
Doesn't look like
there's anything.

275
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:53,267
Did you see anything?

276
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:56,600
Nothing stood out
to me earlier either.

277
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:59,367
You, Robles?
Did you spot anything?

278
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:01,733
No, Bok, nothing earlier either.

279
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:04,400
Nothing.

280
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:08,800
Maybe the kidnapper just
really died...

281
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:11,233
Maybe he was sick.
Looked sickly too.

282
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:14,933
Probably just the mayor
being paranoid.

283
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:20,500
Chief's calling.

284
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:23,100
Let's go.

285
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:27,900
Let's call the rest of the team.

286
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:29,500
We'll come back later.

287
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,900
Mayor.

288
00:18:57,933 --> 00:19:00,267
How was your big break,
Miss Mira?

289
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:02,467
Oh, it certainly helped, Mayor.

290
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,067
Our editor-in-chief
has been assigning me

291
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,400
to bigger assignments.

292
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,433
Well...

293
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:13,767
I guess this is the part

294
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:17,500
where you going to tell me what
favor I need to do in return...

295
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:20,100
for the one favor you gave me.

296
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:26,767
Mira...

297
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:28,933
That's why I like you.

298
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,333
Ces!

299
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,033
Long time!

300
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:40,033
How are you?

301
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:44,233
It's glad to have you back,
Lieutenant Conde.

302
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,700
Thank you, Doc.

303
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,333
Oh, Sergeant Enriquez...

304
00:19:48,467 --> 00:19:51,533
this is Dr. Cecilia Montero.

305
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:53,567
She's our medicolegal expert

306
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:56,067
we often work with
at the station.

307
00:19:56,933 --> 00:19:58,867
Good to have you on board.

308
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:02,167
It's an honor, Doctor Montero.

309
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:04,267
Just call me Ces.

310
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:07,000
Anyway, team,

311
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:08,667
how's the progress on
your assignments?

312
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:10,267
Sir, we still haven't seen...

313
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:15,267
any suspicious characters
in the CCTV footage.

314
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:18,133
Unless this was an inside job.

315
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:22,567
But nothing points
to that either, Sir.

316
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:24,833
We even considered the
malpractice angle...

317
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:27,400
but that came up negative too.

318
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:31,100
We couldn't find any records
at all about this person.

319
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:34,633
But SOCO found an address
scribbled...

320
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,833
on a piece of paper
in Batsi's stuff.

321
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:39,800
Problem is, no context.

322
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:43,067
Later, check that out
with Robles, all right?

323
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:48,600
Sir, Robles and I already have
a lot on our plate today.

324
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:53,233
Conde, you and Enriquez
handle it.

325
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:55,067
Yes, Sir.

326
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,933
Yes, Sir.

327
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,000
Pretty sure they'll just be
wasting their time

328
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,033
on that address.

329
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:05,300
Doc, we need your help.

330
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:07,167
I'll do my best, Chief.

331
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:08,700
Thank you, Doc.

332
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:14,900
Our problem here

333
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:16,733
is the timeline...

334
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:19,700
because we still have to
wait a few days

335
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,533
for the autopsy results.

336
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:22,800
It depends, Chief.

337
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:24,033
It's case-to-case

338
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:26,733
Oh, Doc, can we rush it?

339
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:28,600
The Mayor's putting
pressure on me.

340
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:29,400
Yes, Chief.

341
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,567
Was this really how he looked
when he died?

342
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,100
Yes, Doc.

343
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:43,233
Right after he had a seizure,

344
00:21:43,367 --> 00:21:45,067
it's like he felt
intense pain...

345
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,200
then his body stiffened.

346
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:49,700
The initial report from the
doctor says cardiac arrest.

347
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:52,267
But, Doctor, what do you think?

348
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:55,733
I think we can get the results
sooner than expected.

349
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:57,267
That's good.

350
00:21:59,567 --> 00:22:02,200
While we're waiting for
the report from the Doctor...

351
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,433
check the address first.

352
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:06,200
Maybe we'll find something
there.

353
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:07,467
Yes, Sir.

354
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,367
Yes, Sir.

355
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,400
This is the address.

356
00:22:27,367 --> 00:22:28,633
You think we'll get any answers

357
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:30,300
from Doctor Montero?

358
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:32,200
Yes, she's good.

359
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:34,067
And she's pretty too.

360
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:38,733
You are pretty too.

361
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,000
Just fix yourself up a bit.

362
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:47,200
Looks like there's
no one home, Right?

363
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,000
All right, I'll check
the perimeter, Sir.

364
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:53,733
Good idea.

365
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,567
Don't arrest me.

366
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,200
I have nothing to do with this.

367
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:17,300
Nothing to do?

368
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:19,133
Aren't you here because of
what happened

369
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:21,167
to the Mayor's daughter's
kidnapping?

370
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:24,133
What do you know about
the kidnapping?

371
00:23:25,233 --> 00:23:26,367
You know Batsi?

372
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,100
No, I mean, he's just
a friend of Sonny.

373
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:29,667
Who's Sonny?

374
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:32,100
One of the kidnappers

375
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:34,267
you brought to the hospital.

376
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,867
That's Sonny.
He's my boyfriend.

377
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,600
Lieutenant Conde!

378
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:41,633
What's going on?

379
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:05,433
Strychnine poisoning.

380
00:24:05,567 --> 00:24:06,667
The test came back positive.

381
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,000
Someone poisoned Sonny.

382
00:24:08,133 --> 00:24:09,533
Wait, That's familiar to me,
Doc.

383
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:10,867
Why's that, Sergeant Enriquez?

384
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,300
I saw it in one of Amo's
old movies, Sir.

385
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:14,767
Follow your lead, Sergeant.

386
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,100
But make sure

387
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:17,967
Amo doesn't catch wind

388
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:19,567
that we're investigating him.

389
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:20,233
Yes, Sir!

390
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:21,267
Are you telling me

391
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,633
with all the people
in this hospital

392
00:24:23,767 --> 00:24:25,433
not a single lead came out of
your investigation?

393
00:24:25,567 --> 00:24:27,833
We're really sorry,
but please believe us

394
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:29,200
we're doing everything we can

395
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:32,400
to get to the bottom of
your child's kidnapping.

396
00:24:32,533 --> 00:24:33,667
We have a problem.

397
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:34,833
Now what?

398
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,100
I want to know what you think

399
00:24:36,233 --> 00:24:37,833
about Amo's connection

400
00:24:37,967 --> 00:24:39,500
to the cases we're working on.

401
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:40,867
Do you have any suggestions?

402
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,933
Or maybe you want to help me.
